I worked in the VGR (Vision Graphics and Robotics) laboratory at York University to develop a prototype of a 3D GPS software. The software could be used by Emergency Medical Services to better navigate the streets, and also featured a VR component with the ability to use the software in VR. Using game development software: Unity and programs such as Sketch Up for 3D modelling, we worked to build a prototype. The language used was C#.
